# CTO Recommendation (One Major Improvement)

After writing this article, I believe we have reached a point where byDebut is evolving beyond a software architecture into a **constitutional platform architecture**.

I would therefore introduce a concept that I have not suggested before:

## **Constitutional Objects**

Not every object in the system has the same importance.

I would classify them into three tiers:

### Tier 1 — Constitutional Objects (Immutable Foundation)

* Story Passport
* Story DNA
* Story Lineage
* Rights Holder
* Attribution
* Governance Rules

These are protected by the Constitution. Every service depends on them.

### Tier 2 — Core Domain Objects

* Story Portal
* Organizations
* Reader Profiles
* AI Editorial Workspaces
* Creative Sessions
* Timeline Graphs
* Analytics

These implement the business but remain subordinate to the constitutional objects.

### Tier 3 — Operational Objects

* Notifications
* Comments
* Search Indexes
* Recommendations
* Temporary AI Jobs
* Caches
* UI Preferences
* Logs

These may evolve freely without affecting the constitutional integrity of the platform.

I believe documenting this hierarchy later (perhaps as an ADR and as part of the Domain Model) will make Claude Code's implementation much cleaner. It gives engineers a clear understanding of which entities are foundational and must be treated with exceptional care, and which are operational and can evolve more rapidly. This distinction will become increasingly valuable as byDebut grows beyond the Gemini XPRIZE MVP into a large-scale platform.
